Related reference
Sample: Hello World Pod-Loader on page 34
Creating a Pod using a PodLoader
The next step is to create the PodLoader class. The PodLoader extends the class
curam.cefwidgets.pods.pod.impl.PodLoader and implements the createPod
method. Create a new class on the Server by copying this example into a class named
HelloWorld in the package pods.loaders.
A very simple PodLoader:
001  package pods.podloaders;
002
003  import java.util.Map;
004  import org.w3c.dom.Document;
005  import org.w3c.dom.Node;
006  import curam.cefwidgets.docbuilder.impl.PodBuilder;
007  import curam.cefwidgets.pods.pod.impl.PodLoader;
